程序包 org.modelmapper

类 TypeToken<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.modelmapper.TypeToken<T>
  • 类型参数:
    T - Represented type
    public class TypeToken<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a generic type T. Subclassing TypeToken allows for type information to be preserved at runtime.

    Example: To create a type literal for List<String>, you can create an empty anonymous inner class:

    TypeToken<List<String>> list = new TypeToken<List<String>>();

      • getRawType

        public final java.lang.Class<T> getRawType()
        Returns the raw type for T.
        • If T is a Class, T itself is returned.
        • If T is a ParameterizedType, the raw type is returned
        • If T is a GenericArrayType, the raw type is returned
        • If T is a TypeVariable or WildcardType, the raw type of the first upper bound is returned
